2. What are the admission requirements for international students at UCAM Catholic University of Murcia?
Admission requirements for international students at UCAM vary depending on the program of study. Generally, applicants must provide academic transcripts, standardized test scores, English language proficiency test scores, letters of recommendation, and a personal statement. It is important to review the specific admission criteria outlined by UCAM and seek guidance from Qadri International Educational Consultants for personalized assistance.

3. Are scholarships available for international students at UCAM Catholic University of Murcia?
UCAM offers various scholarships and financial aid options to eligible students, including merit-based scholarships, need-based scholarships, and grants. Additionally, students may explore external scholarship opportunities, student loans, and work-study programs to help finance their education. Qadri International Educational Consultants can provide guidance on scholarship opportunities and financial aid options available to international students.

4. Can I work part-time while studying at UCAM Catholic University of Murcia?
International students studying at UCAM may be eligible to work part-time during their studies, subject to certain restrictions and regulations. The Spanish government allows international students to work up to 20 hours per week during the academic year and full-time during scheduled breaks and holidays. However, it is important to check the specific work regulations and visa requirements for international students in Spain and consult with Qadri International Educational Consultants for guidance on employment opportunities.
